 Billing and metrics are delayed. Accept this fact, and plan your project around it. All platforms (AWS / GCP etc.) have this issue, simply because it's too expensive to calculate billing in real time, and services can scale rapidly!

 Use "Google Cloud Monitoring"
 
 
Do not use Cloud Run with default settings. Set max_instances = 1 when you're deploying a service for the first, even tenth time! Unless the service needs to scale, keep the instances low. Had we begun with this, our cost in worst case scenario would have been $72 only (72000/ 1000 max instances)


